ork=Billboard}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"[[Sweet but Psycho]]\" \n| Choice Song: Pop\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Spotify|Spotify Awards]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2020\n| Herself\n| Most-Streamed EDM Female Artist\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nacionrex.com/amp/musica/spotify-awards-200-nominados-categorias-finalistas-premios-20200219-0007.html|title=Conoce a todos los nominados a los Spotify Awards 2020|author=Reyes, Van|date=February 19, 2020|website=nacionrex.com|accessdate=February 22, 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|1=http://www.avamax.com}}\n\n{{Ava Max}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Max, Ava}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Albanian descent]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Albanian singers]]<!-- Max's ethnicity allows for the category to remain. Do not remove without seeking consensus at the talk page. -->\n[[Category:Musicians from Milwaukee]]\n[[Category:Singers from Virginia]]\n[[Category:LGBT singers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT songwriters]]\n[[Category:LGBT women]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Virginia]]\n[[Category:MTV EMA winners]]\n[[Category:American_pop_singers]]\n", "name_user": "Ss112", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAs lead artist:updated", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ava_Max"}
{"title_page": "Fin de Partie", "text_new": "{{For|the Samuel Beckett play|Endgame (play)}}\n{{short description|2018 opera by Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g}}\n\n{{Infobox opera \n| name              = Fin de partie\n| genre_header      = Opera\n| image             = \n| image_upright     = \n| based_on = {{based on|''[[Endgame (play)|Endgame]]''|[[Samuel Beckett]]}}\n| caption           = \n| composer          = [[Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g]]\n| librettist        = Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g\n| premiere_date     = 15 November 2018 \n| premiere_location = {{Nowrap|Teatro alla Scala,<br> Milan}}\n}}\n\n'''''Fin de partie''''' is a one-act opera by [[Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g]], set to a French-language [[libretto]] adapted by the composer from the play ''[[Endgame (play)|Endgame]]'' (French title: ''Fin de partie'') by [[Samuel Beckett]], with the inclusion of a setting of Beckett's English-language poem 'Roundelay' at the start of the opera.<ref name=\"Clements\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/19/fin-de-partie-la-scala-milan-review-gyorgy-kurtag-samuel-beckett | title=''Fin de Partie'' review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's compelling musical testament | author=Andrew Clements | work=The Guardian | date=19 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>  Kurt\u00e1g fully titled this work, his first opera, as follows:<ref name=\"Maddocks\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/24/fin-de-partie-gyorgy-kurtag-la-scala-milan-review-war-requiem-eno-britten-wolfgang-tillmans | title=''Fin de partie'' review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's thrilling endgame | author=Fiona Maddocks | work=The Observer | date=24 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n: ''Samuel Beckett: Fin de partie: sc\u00e8nes et monologues, op\u00e9ra en un acte''\n\nKurt\u00e1g dedicated the opera to the memory of \"''mon professeur'' [[Ferenc Farkas]] \" and of \"mon ami Tam\u00e1s Blum\":\n\n: \"''qui, dans ma jeunesse, m'ont appri sur l'essentiel sur l'op\u00e9ra''\"\n: (\"who, in my youth, taught me the essentials of opera\")\n\n==History==\nThe [[Teatro alla Scala]], Milan commissioned the opera, and staged the premiere on 15 November 2018.<ref name=\"Clements\"/><ref name=\"Maddocks\"/><ref name=\"Woolfe\">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/16/arts/music/review-kurtag-endgame-opera.html | title=Review: A 92-Year-Old Composer's ''Endgame'' Opera Is Patiently Perfect | author=Zachary Woolfe | work=The New York Times | date=7 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>  The director of the premiere production was [[Pierre Audi]], with set and costume designs by Christof Hetzer, and lighting design by Urs Sch\u00f6nebaum.  The premiere production is a joint production between La Scala and Dutch National Opera (DNO), Amsterdam.  The second production of the opera is scheduled for DNO in March 2019.\n\nUpon the recommendation of [[Gy\u00f6rgy Ligeti]],<ref name=\"Ross\">{{cite news | url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/12/24/gyorgy-kurtag-with-his-opera-of-endgame-proves-to-be-becketts-equal | title= Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g, with his Opera of ''Endgame'', Proves To Be Beckett\u2019s Equal | author=Alex Ross | work=The New Yorker | date=24 December 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref> Kurt\u00e1g had seen a production of Beckett's play in Paris in 1957.<ref name=\"Maddocks\"/>  This experience greatly affected Kurt\u00e1g, which he described to the American music critic Jeremy Eichler as \"one of the strongest experiences of my life\".<ref name=\"Ross\"/>  For his opera, Kurt\u00e1g condensed the play, retaining around 60% of the French text.<ref name=\"Clements\"/>  He has acknowledged his studies of the operas of [[Claudio Monteverdi]] as inspiration for his own opera.<ref name=\"Karasz\">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/07/arts/music/gyorgy-kurtag-opera.html | title=A 92-Year-Old Composer's First Opera Is His ''Endgame'' | author=Palko Karasz | work=The New York Times | date=7 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe original commission for the work arrived in 2010 from La Scala.  Kurt\u00e1g initially wished there to be no contract and no commission fee.<ref name=\"Karasz\"/>  The Ernst von Siemens Music Foundation provided financial support for the commission.  Kurt\u00e1g spent 8 years on the composition of the opera, with assistance from his wife Marta.<ref name=\"Karasz\"/>  Kurt\u00e1g did not attend the world premiere performance because his frail health rendered him unable to travel from Budapest to Milan.<ref name=\"Clements\"/><ref name=\"Maddocks\"/>\n\n==Roles==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Role\n![[Voice type]]\n!Premiere cast,<br/>[[Teatro alla Scala]], Milan<br/>15 November 2018<br/>(Conductor: [[Markus Stenz]])\n|-\n|Hamm\n|bass-baritone\n|Frode Olsen\n|-\n|Clov, Hamm's servant\n|[[baritone]]\n|Leigh Melrose\n|-\n|Nell, Hamm's mother\n|[[contralto]]\n|[[Hilary Summers]]\n|-\n|Nagg, Hamm's father\n|[[tenor]] buffo\n|Leonardo Cortellazzi\n|-\n|}\n\n==Synopsis==\n{{prose|section|date=January 2019}}\nThe setting is a house by the sea, where four people reside:\n*Hamm, an elderly gentleman confined to a wheelchair\n*Clov, servant to Hamm, who cannot sit down\n*Nagg and Nell, Hamm's very old parents, each trapped in a dustbin, without legs\n\nThe tensions between the four characters exasperate each of them:\n*Hamm cannot abide his parents and their chatter.\n*Nell can barely tolerate Nagg.\n*Clov regards the others wearily. \nAll four wait for an end to the inertia and claustrophobia of their situation.\n\n# Prologue: Nell is the first character to appear, and delivers the setting of 'Roundelay' to begin the opera.  Her words hazily allude to memories, with the sound of footsteps as the only sound to be heard on the beach.\n# Clov's Pantomime:  Clov and Hamm appear.  Clov is troubled and uneasy on his legs.  He makes repetitive gestures, the same gestures every day, during his domestic chores, interspersed with short, nervous laughter.\n# Clov's First Monologue:  Clov speaks of the possibility that the current situation may come to some sort of end soon.\n# Hamm's First Monologue:  by contrast, Hamm thinks about his and his parents' sufferings.  With feelings of despondency and exhaustion, he claims that he cannot resolve the current circumstances.\n# Bin:  Nagg and Nell, both severely handicapped, are tired out from their long-term bickering, and their mutual incomprehension.  During their conversation, they recall the cycling accident in the Ardennes that caused them both to lose their legs.  Memories also surface of a boat trip on Lake Como.  These memories are their sole happy memories and, at least superficially, give them a little nostalgia for their life spent together.  Yet, Hamm, who wants to sleep, finds his parents' chatter irritating, and orders Clov to throw the bins, including Nagg and Nell, into the sea.  Nell dies in the meantime, apparently unnoticed by the others.\n# Novel: Hamm wants to tell Nagg a story.  In past days, a father had come to him on Christmas Eve asking for bread for his son.  Hamm had decided to take him on.\n# Nagg's Monologue:  Nagg remembers when Hamm was young and needed him.\n# Hamm's Penultimate Monologue:  Hamm ponders his difficult relations with others.\n# Hamm and Clov's Dialogue:  Hamm asks Clov for his tranquilliser.  Clov replies that no tranquillisers are left. \n# \"It's over, Clov\" and Clov's Vaudeville:  Hamm tells Clov that he no longer needs him, but then asks Clov to say something that he may remember before departing.  Clov remarks that Hamm had never spoken to him until that moment.  Only now, as he is about to leave, does Hamm pay any notice of him. \n# Clov's Last Monologue:  Clov reflects on his condition.  He has never understood what words like 'love' and 'friendship' mean.  He also feels old, tired, and unable to form new habits.  He is bound to his repetitive, never-changing daily routine.\n# Transition to the Finale:  Hamm thanks Clov as Clov is about to leave.\n# Hamm's Last Monologue:  Clov is about to leave, but has not yet moved.  Hamm realises that he has been left alone. \n# Epilogue:  Hamm grasps that it is now up to him \u2013 and him alone \u2013 to continue playing the endgame.\n\n==Reception==\nBoth Andrew Clements<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/19/fin-de-partie-la-scala-milan-review-gyorgy-kurtag-samuel-beckett|title=Fin de Partie review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's compelling musical testament|last=Clements|first=Andrew|date=2018-11-19|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-10-12|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> and Fiona Maddocks<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/24/fin-de-partie-gyorgy-kurtag-la-scala-milan-review-war-requiem-eno-britten-wolfgang-tillmans|title=Fin de partie review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's thrilling endgame|last=Maddocks|first=Fiona|date=2018-11-24|work=The Observer|access-date=2019-10-12|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref> of ''[[The Guardian]]'' awarded ''Fin de partie'' a full five stars. Alex Ross stated in ''[[The New Yorker]]'' that \u201cit seems the equal of the celebrated text on which it is based. Beckett has been waiting for Kurt\u00e1g all this time.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/12/24/gyorgy-kurtag-with-his-opera-of-endgame-proves-to-be-becketts-equal|title=Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g, with his Opera of \"Endgame,\" Proves To Be Beckett\u2019s Equal|last=Ross|first=Alex|date=2018-12-17|access-date=2019-10-12|language=en|issn=0028-792X}}</ref> The opera later ranked fourth in a poll by ''The Guardian'' of the greatest 21st century works of classical music.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/sep/12/best-classical-music-works-of-the-21st-century|title=The best classical music works of the 21st century|last=Clements|first=Andrew|date=2019-09-12|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-10-12|last2=Maddocks|first2=Fiona|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|last3=Lewis|first3=John|last4=Molleson|first4=Kate|last5=Service|first5=Tom|last6=Jeal|first6=Erica|last7=Ashley|first7=Tim}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20190506184233/http://www.teatroallascala.org/en/season/2017-2018/opera/fin-de-partie.html Teatro alla Scala page on ''Fin de Partie'']\n* [http://static.teatroallascala.org/static/upload/lib/libretto_2018_findepartie.pdf Libretto of Fin de partie]\n* [http://static.teatroallascala.org/static/upload/syn/synopsis_2018_findepartie.pdf Teatro alla Scala, English-language synopsis of Fin de partie]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fin de partie}}\n[[Category:Compositions by Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g]]\n[[Category:2018 operas]]\n[[Category:French-language operas]]\n[[Category:Opera world premieres at La Scala]]\n[[Category:Operas based on plays]]\n[[Category:Samuel Beckett]]\n[[Category:Operas]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 opera by Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g}}\n{{For|the Samuel Beckett play|Endgame (play)}}\n\n{{Infobox opera \n| name              = Fin de partie\n| genre_header      = Opera\n| image             = \n| image_upright     = \n| based_on = {{based on|''[[Endgame (play)|Endgame]]''|[[Samuel Beckett]]}}\n| caption           = \n| composer          = [[Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g]]\n| librettist        = Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g\n| premiere_date     = 15 November 2018 \n| premiere_location = {{Nowrap|Teatro alla Scala,<br> Milan}}\n}}\n\n'''''Fin de partie''''' is a one-act opera by [[Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g]], set to a French-language [[libretto]] adapted by the composer from the play ''[[Endgame (play)|Endgame]]'' (French title: ''Fin de partie'') by [[Samuel Beckett]], with the inclusion of a setting of Beckett's English-language poem 'Roundelay' at the start of the opera.<ref name=\"Clements\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/19/fin-de-partie-la-scala-milan-review-gyorgy-kurtag-samuel-beckett | title=''Fin de Partie'' review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's compelling musical testament | author=Andrew Clements | work=The Guardian | date=19 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>  Kurt\u00e1g fully titled this work, his first opera, as follows: <ref name=\"Maddocks\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/24/fin-de-partie-gyorgy-kurtag-la-scala-milan-review-war-requiem-eno-britten-wolfgang-tillmans | title=''Fin de partie'' review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's thrilling endgame | author=Fiona Maddocks | work=The Observer | date=24 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n: ''Samuel Beckett: Fin de partie: sc\u00e8nes et monologues, op\u00e9ra en un acte''  \n\nKurt\u00e1g dedicated the opera to the memory of \"''mon professeur'' [[Ferenc Farkas]] \" and of \"mon ami Tam\u00e1s Blum\":\n\n: \"''qui, dans ma jeunesse, m'ont appri sur l'essentiel sur l'op\u00e9ra''\"\n: (\"who, in my youth, taught me the essentials of opera\")\n\n==History==\nThe [[Teatro alla Scala]], Milan commissioned the opera, and staged the premiere on 15 November 2018.<ref name=\"Clements\"/><ref name=\"Maddocks\"/><ref name=\"Woolfe\">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/16/arts/music/review-kurtag-endgame-opera.html | title=Review: A 92-Year-Old Composer's ''Endgame'' Opera Is Patiently Perfect | author=Zachary Woolfe | work=The New York Times | date=7 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>  The director of the premiere production was [[Pierre Audi]], with set and costume designs by Christof Hetzer, and lighting design by Urs Sch\u00f6nebaum.  The premiere production is a joint production between La Scala and Dutch National Opera (DNO), Amsterdam.  The second production of the opera is scheduled for DNO in March 2019.\n\nUpon the recommendation of [[Gy\u00f6rgy Ligeti]],<ref name=\"Ross\">{{cite news | url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/12/24/gyorgy-kurtag-with-his-opera-of-endgame-proves-to-be-becketts-equal | title= Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g, with his Opera of ''Endgame'', Proves To Be Beckett\u2019s Equal | author=Alex Ross | work=The New Yorker | date=24 December 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref> Kurt\u00e1g had seen a production of Beckett's play in Paris in 1957.<ref name=\"Maddocks\"/>  This experience greatly affected Kurt\u00e1g, which he described to the American music critic Jeremy Eichler as \"one of the strongest experiences of my life\".<ref name=\"Ross\"/>.  For his opera, Kurt\u00e1g condensed the play, retaining around 60% of the French text.<ref name=\"Clements\"/>  He has acknowledged his studies of the operas of [[Claudio Monteverdi]] as inspiration for his own opera.<ref name=\"Karasz\">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/07/arts/music/gyorgy-kurtag-opera.html | title=A 92-Year-Old Composer's First Opera Is His ''Endgame'' | author=Palko Karasz | work=The New York Times | date=7 November 2018 | accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>  \n\nThe original commission for the work arrived in 2010 from La Scala.  Kurt\u00e1g initially wished there to be no contract and no commission fee.<ref name=\"Karasz\"/>  The Ernst von Siemens Music Foundation provided financial support for the commission.  Kurt\u00e1g spent 8 years on the composition of the opera, with assistance from his wife Marta.<ref name=\"Karasz\"/>  Kurt\u00e1g did not attend the world premiere performance because his frail health rendered him unable to travel from Budapest to Milan.<ref name=\"Clements\"/><ref name=\"Maddocks\"/>\n\n==Roles==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Role\n![[Voice type]]\n!Premiere cast,<br/>[[Teatro alla Scala]], Milan<br/>15 November 2018<br/>(Conductor: [[Markus Stenz]])\n|-\n|Hamm\n|bass-baritone\n|Frode Olsen\n|-\n|Clov, Hamm's servant\n|[[baritone]]\n|Leigh Melrose\n|-\n|Nell, Hamm's mother\n|[[contralto]]\n|[[Hilary Summers]]\n|-\n|Nagg, Hamm's father\n|[[tenor]] buffo\n|Leonardo Cortellazzi\n|-\n|}\n\n==Synopsis==\n{{prose|section|date=January 2019}}\nThe setting is a house by the sea, where four people reside:\n*Hamm, an elderly gentleman confined to a wheelchair\n*Clov, servant to Hamm, who cannot sit down\n*Nagg and Nell, Hamm's very old parents, each trapped in a dustbin, without legs\n\nThe tensions between the four characters exasperate each of them:\n*Hamm cannot abide his parents and their chatter.\n*Nell can barely tolerate Nagg.\n*Clov regards the others wearily. \nAll four wait for an end to the inertia and claustrophobia of their situation.\n\n# Prologue: Nell is the first character to appear, and delivers the setting of 'Roundelay' to begin the opera.  Her words hazily allude to memories, with the sound of footsteps as the only sound to be heard on the beach.\n# Clov's Pantomime:  Clov and Hamm appear.  Clov is troubled and uneasy on his legs.  He makes repetitive gestures, the same gestures every day, during his domestic chores, interspersed with short, nervous laughter.\n# Clov's First Monologue:  Clov speaks of the possibility that the current situation may come to some sort of end soon.\n# Hamm's First Monologue:  by contrast, Hamm thinks about his and his parents' sufferings.  With feelings of despondency and exhaustion, he claims that he cannot resolve the current circumstances.\n# Bin:  Nagg and Nell, both severely handicapped, are tired out from their long-term bickering, and their mutual incomprehension.  During their conversation, they recall the cycling accident in the Ardennes that caused them both to lose their legs.  Memories also surface of a boat trip on Lake Como.  These memories are their sole happy memories and, at least superficially, give them a little nostalgia for their life spent together.  Yet, Hamm, who wants to sleep, finds his parents' chatter irritating, and orders Clov to throw the bins, including Nagg and Nell, into the sea.  Nell dies in the meantime, apparently unnoticed by the others.\n# Novel: Hamm wants to tell Nagg a story.  In past days, a father had come to him on Christmas Eve asking for bread for his son.  Hamm had decided to take him on.\n# Nagg's Monologue:  Nagg remembers when Hamm was young and needed him.\n# Hamm's Penultimate Monologue:  Hamm ponders his difficult relations with others.\n# Hamm and Clov's Dialogue:  Hamm asks Clov for his tranquilliser.  Clov replies that no tranquillisers are left. \n# \"It's over, Clov\" and Clov's Vaudeville:  Hamm tells Clov that he no longer needs him, but then asks Clov to say something that he may remember before departing.  Clov remarks that Hamm had never spoken to him until that moment.  Only now, as he is about to leave, does Hamm pay any notice of him. \n# Clov's Last Monologue:  Clov reflects on his condition.  He has never understood what words like 'love' and 'friendship' mean.  He also feels old, tired, and unable to form new habits.  He is bound to his repetitive, never-changing daily routine.\n# Transition to the Finale:  Hamm thanks Clov as Clov is about to leave.\n# Hamm's Last Monologue:  Clov is about to leave, but has not yet moved.  Hamm realises that he has been left alone. \n# Epilogue:  Hamm grasps that it is now up to him \u2013 and him alone \u2013 to continue playing the endgame.\n\n==Reception==\nBoth Andrew Clements<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/19/fin-de-partie-la-scala-milan-review-gyorgy-kurtag-samuel-beckett|title=Fin de Partie review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's compelling musical testament|last=Clements|first=Andrew|date=2018-11-19|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-10-12|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> and Fiona Maddocks<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/nov/24/fin-de-partie-gyorgy-kurtag-la-scala-milan-review-war-requiem-eno-britten-wolfgang-tillmans|title=Fin de partie review \u2013 Kurt\u00e1g's thrilling endgame|last=Maddocks|first=Fiona|date=2018-11-24|work=The Observer|access-date=2019-10-12|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref> of ''[[The Guardian]]'' awarded ''Fin de partie'' a full five stars. Alex Ross stated in ''[[The New Yorker]]'' that \u201cit seems the equal of the celebrated text on which it is based. Beckett has been waiting for Kurt\u00e1g all this time.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/12/24/gyorgy-kurtag-with-his-opera-of-endgame-proves-to-be-becketts-equal|title=Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g, with his Opera of \u201cEndgame,\u201d Proves To Be Beckett\u2019s Equal|last=Ross|first=Alex|date=2018-12-17|access-date=2019-10-12|language=en|issn=0028-792X}}</ref> The opera later ranked fourth in a poll by ''The Guardian'' of the greatest 21st century works of classical music.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/sep/12/best-classical-music-works-of-the-21st-century|title=The best classical music works of the 21st century|last=Clements|first=Andrew|date=2019-09-12|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-10-12|last2=Maddocks|first2=Fiona|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|last3=Lewis|first3=John|last4=Molleson|first4=Kate|last5=Service|first5=Tom|last6=Jeal|first6=Erica|last7=Ashley|first7=Tim}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20190506184233/http://www.teatroallascala.org/en/season/2017-2018/opera/fin-de-partie.html Teatro alla Scala page on ''Fin de Partie'']\n* [http://static.teatroallascala.org/static/upload/lib/libretto_2018_findepartie.pdf Libretto of Fin de partie]\n* [http://static.teatroallascala.org/static/upload/syn/synopsis_2018_findepartie.pdf Teatro alla Scala, English-language synopsis of Fin de partie]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fin de partie}}\n[[Category:Compositions by Gy\u00f6rgy Kurt\u00e1g]]\n[[Category:2018 operas]]\n[[Category:French-language operas]]\n[[Category: Opera world premieres at La Scala]]\n[[Category:Operas based on plays]]\n[[Category:Samuel Beckett]]\n[[Category:Operas]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fin_de_Partie"}
{"title_page": "Adolphe Vorderman", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name                      = {{nowrap|Adolphe Guillaume Vorderman}}\n| image                     = A G Vorderman.jpg\n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_date                = {{Birth date|1844|12|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place               = [[The Hague]], [[Netherlands]]\n| death_date                = {{Death date and age|1902|6|15|1844|12|12|df=yes}}\n| death_place               = [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]], [[Dutch East Indies]]<br/><small>(now [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]])</small>\n| nationality               = Dutch\n| education                 = \n| alma_mater                = \n| occupation                = Physician \n| years_active              = \n| employer                  = \n| organization              = \n| known_for                 = Research into [[beriberi]]\n| notable_works             = \n| spouse                    = \n| partner                   = \n| children                  = \n| parents                   = \n| relatives                 = [[Carol Vorderman]] (great-granddaughter)\n}}\n'''Adolphe Guillaume Vorderman''' (12 December 1844&nbsp;\u2013 15 July 1902) was a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] [[physician]] and [[scientist]] whose extensive and scrupulous study<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorderman |first=A.G. |year=1897 |title=Onderzoek naar het verband tusschen den aard der rijstvoeding in de gevangenissen op Java en Madoera en het voorkomen van beri-beri onder de ge\u00efnterneerden |trans-title=Research into the link between the nature of the rice diet in prisons in Java and Madura and the prevention of beriberi among the internees |location=[[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]] |publisher=Jav. Boekh. & Drukkerij |language=nl }}</ref> of the link between polished rice and [[beriberi]] in the [[Dutch East Indies]] in 1897 helped lead to the discovery of vitamins. His great-granddaughter is [[British people|British]] television presenter [[Carol Vorderman]].\n\n==Biography==\nVorderman, who was born in [[The Hague]], first travelled to the Dutch East Indies in 1866 as a Naval Medical Officer. In 1871 he joined the Civil Health Department, and was stationed at [[Sumenep (city)|Sumenep]] on the island of [[Madura Island|Madura]] until 1881 when he was transferred to [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]] (now [[Jakarta]]). From 1890 until his death in [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]], he served as Chief Inspector of the department.<ref name=\"nationaalherbarium\">{{cite web |url= http://www.nationaalherbarium.nl/fmcollectors/V/VordermanAG.htm |title=Vorderman A.G. |work=[[National Herbarium of the Netherlands]] |year=2007 |accessdate=11 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Beriberi study===\nIn 1883 the Dutch government sent [[Christiaan Eijkman]] to the [[Dutch East Indies]] (now [[Indonesia]]) to try to determine the cause of and find a cure for beriberi. He noticed that chickens fed polished rice&nbsp;\u2013 which is rice which has had its bran removed&nbsp;\u2013 developed a similar paralysis in their legs. Before he could follow up on this line of enquiry, ill health forced him to return home to the [[Netherlands]]. Before leaving he asked his friend Adolphe Vorderman, who was Chief Medical Officer, to continue the research on the link between rice and the disease.\n\nVorderman, who had already noted that beriberi occurred a lot in some prisons, but very little in others, decided to conduct a preliminary survey of the type of rice served in a sample of prisons. When that initial study seemed to confirm a link, he decided to conduct a complete study of all prisons.\n\nIn 1897 Vorderman visited all of the around 100 prisons on the island of Java. He took samples of the prison rice and examined the prison records to determine the number of beriberi cases. He kept the real purpose of his visits secret so that word did not get around the Chinese rice suppliers and lead them to change the type of rice they provided.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Vandenbroucke |first=Jan P. |year=2013 |title=Adolphe Vorderman's 1897 study on beriberi: an example of scrupulous efforts to avoid bias |journal=Journal of the Royal Society of Medicine |volume=106 |issue=3 |pages=108\u2013111 |doi=10.1177/0141076813478790 |pmid=23481433 |pmc=3595404 }}</ref>\n\nLater he conducted blind testing with rice experts to discover the make-up and origin of the rice varieties he found in the prison samples.\n\nVorderman found that in the prisons using mostly brown rice, the incidence of beriberi was less than 1 in 10,000. In the prisons serving mainly polished white rice the proportion was 1 in 39. In his published report, he concluded that this marked difference could not be explained by any other nutritional or sanitary factor.\n\nLater others, including [[Gerrit Grijns]], took over the research which ultimately led to the discovery of [[vitamins]]. In the case of beriberi, the vitamin that was lost when the [[bran]] was removed was [[thiamin]]&nbsp;\u2013 vitamin B<sub>1</sub>.\n\nIn a 2007 episode of the [[BBC]] [[genealogy|genealogical]] documentary series ''[[Who Do You Think You Are? (British TV series)|Who Do You Think You Are?]]'', Carol Vorderman researched her great grandfather Adolphe.  In the episode, the Director of the [[Eijkman Institute]] stated his opinion that had he still been alive at the time, Adolphe Vorderman should have shared the [[Nobel Prize in Medicine]] with Eijkman and [[Sir Frederick Hopkins]], who were awarded the prize in 1929 for their vitamin-related work. During the programme, there was no discussion on whether the dead can be awarded the Nobel Prize.\n\n===Other work===\nApart from his nutritional study Voordeman published papers on local poisons, drugs, foods and birds, and was a collector of botanical specimens. For his work he was made an honorary [[Doctor of Science]] by [[Utrecht University]]. The tree species ''[[Myristica]] vordermanni'' was named in his honour by [[Otto Warburg (botanist)|Otto Warburg]].<ref name=\"nationaalherbarium\"/> Vorderman became a corresponding member of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 1889.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.dwc.knaw.nl/biografie/pmknaw/?pagetype=authorDetail&aId=PE00003629 |title=Adolphe Guillaume Vorderman (1844\u20131902) |publisher=[[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] |date= |accessdate=25 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web |url= https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/themes/medicine/carpenter/index.html |title=The Nobel Prize and the Discovery of Vitamins |first=Kenneth J. |last=Carpenter |work=nobelprize.org |date=22 June 2004 }}\n* {{cite web |url= https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1929/eijkman-bio.html |title=Christiaan Eijkman - Biography  |work=nobelprize.org |year=2014 }}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071118051415/http://www.jameslindlibrary.org/trial_records/19th_Century/vorderman/vorderman_commentary.html Adolphe Vorderman's 1897 study of beriberi among prison inmates in the Dutch East Indies ]\n*[http://ag-vorderman.blogspot.com/ Adolphe Vorderman] by Gercon Vorderman {{dead link|date=August 2014}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vorderman, Adolphe}}\n[[Category:1844 births]]\n[[Category:1902 deaths]]\n[[Category:Dutch physicians]]\n[[Category:Writers from The Hague]]\n[[Category:Members of the Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name                      = {{nowrap|Adolphe Guillaume Vorderman}}\n| image                     = A G Vorderman.jpg\n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_date                = {{Birth date|1844|12|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place               = [[The Hague]], [[Netherlands]]\n| death_date                = {{Death date and age|1902|6|15|1844|12|12|df=yes}}\n| death_place               = [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]], [[Dutch East Indies]]<br/><small>(now [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]])</small>\n| nationality               = Dutch\n| education                 = \n| alma_mater                = \n| occupation                = Physician \n| years_active              = \n| employer                  = \n| organization              = \n| known_for                 = Research into [[beriberi]]\n| notable_works             = \n| spouse                    = \n| partner                   = \n| children                  = \n| parents                   = \n| relatives                 = [[Carol Vorderman]] (great-granddaughter)\n}}\n'''Adolphe Guillaume Vorderman''' (12 December 1844 in [[The Hague]]&nbsp;\u2013 15 July 1902 in [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]]) was a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] [[physician]] and [[scientist]] whose extensive and scrupulous study<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorderman |first=A.G. |year=1897 |title=Onderzoek naar het verband tusschen den aard der rijstvoeding in de gevangenissen op Java en Madoera en het voorkomen van beri-beri onder de ge\u00efnterneerden |trans-title=Research into the link between the nature of the rice diet in prisons in Java and Madura and the prevention of beriberi among the internees |location=[[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]] |publisher=Jav. Boekh. & Drukkerij |language=nl }}</ref> of the link between polished rice and [[beriberi]] in the [[Dutch East Indies]] in 1897 helped lead to the discovery of vitamins. His great-granddaughter is [[British people|British]] television presenter [[Carol Vorderman]].\n\n==Biography==\nVorderman first travelled to the Dutch East Indies in 1866 as a Naval Medical Officer. In 1871 he joined the Civil Health Department, and was stationed at [[Sumenep (city)|Sumenep]] on the island of [[Madura Island|Madura]] until 1881 when he was transferred to [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]] (now [[Jakarta]]). From 1890 until his death he served as Chief Inspector of the department.<ref name=\"nationaalherbarium\">{{cite web |url= http://www.nationaalherbarium.nl/fmcollectors/V/VordermanAG.htm |title=Vorderman A.G. |work=[[National Herbarium of the Netherlands]] |year=2007 |accessdate=11 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Beriberi study===\nIn 1883 the Dutch government sent [[Christiaan Eijkman]] to the [[Dutch East Indies]] (now [[Indonesia]]) to try to determine the cause of and find a cure for beriberi. He noticed that chickens fed polished rice&nbsp;\u2013 which is rice which has had its bran removed&nbsp;\u2013 developed a similar paralysis in their legs. Before he could follow up on this line of enquiry, ill health forced him to return home to the [[Netherlands]]. Before leaving he asked his friend Adolphe Vorderman, who was Chief Medical Officer, to continue the research on the link between rice and the disease.\n\nVorderman, who had already noted that beriberi occurred a lot in some prisons, but very little in others, decided to conduct a preliminary survey of the type of rice served in a sample of prisons. When that initial study seemed to confirm a link, he decided to conduct a complete study of all prisons.\n\nIn 1897 Vorderman visited all of the around 100 prisons on the island of Java. He took samples of the prison rice and examined the prison records to determine the number of beriberi cases. He kept the real purpose of his visits secret so that word did not get around the Chinese rice suppliers and lead them to change the type of rice they provided.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Vandenbroucke |first=Jan P. |year=2013 |title=Adolphe Vorderman's 1897 study on beriberi: an example of scrupulous efforts to avoid bias |journal=Journal of the Royal Society of Medicine |volume=106 |issue=3 |pages=108\u2013111 |doi=10.1177/0141076813478790 |pmid=23481433 |pmc=3595404 }}</ref>\n\nLater he conducted blind testing with rice experts to discover the make-up and origin of the rice varieties he found in the prison samples.\n\nVorderman found that in the prisons using mostly brown rice, the incidence of beriberi was less than 1 in 10,000. In the prisons serving mainly polished white rice the proportion was 1 in 39. In his published report, he concluded that this marked difference could not be explained by any other nutritional or sanitary factor.\n\nLater others, including [[Gerrit Grijns]], took over the research which ultimately led to the discovery of [[vitamins]]. In the case of beriberi, the vitamin that was lost when the [[bran]] was removed was [[thiamin]]&nbsp;\u2013 vitamin B<sub>1</sub>.\n\nIn a 2007 episode of the [[BBC]] [[genealogy|genealogical]] documentary series ''[[Who Do You Think You Are? (British TV series)|Who Do You Think You Are?]]'', Carol Vorderman researched her great grandfather Adolphe.  In the episode, the Director of the [[Eijkman Institute]] stated his opinion that had he still been alive at the time, Adolphe Vorderman should have shared the [[Nobel Prize in Medicine]] with Eijkman and [[Sir Frederick Hopkins]], who were awarded the prize in 1929 for their vitamin-related work. During the programme, there was no discussion on whether the dead can be awarded the Nobel Prize.\n\n===Other work===\nApart from his nutritional study Voordeman published papers on local poisons, drugs, foods and birds, and was a collector of botanical specimens. For his work he was made an honorary [[Doctor of Science]] by [[Utrecht University]]. The tree species ''[[Myristica]] vordermanni'' was named in his honour by [[Otto Warburg (botanist)|Otto Warburg]].<ref name=\"nationaalherbarium\"/> Vorderman became a corresponding member of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 1889.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.dwc.knaw.nl/biografie/pmknaw/?pagetype=authorDetail&aId=PE00003629 |title=Adolphe Guillaume Vorderman (1844\u20131902) |publisher=[[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] |date= |accessdate=25 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web |url= https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/themes/medicine/carpenter/index.html |title=The Nobel Prize and the Discovery of Vitamins |first=Kenneth J. |last=Carpenter |work=nobelprize.org |date=22 June 2004 }}\n* {{cite web |url= https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1929/eijkman-bio.html |title=Christiaan Eijkman - Biography  |work=nobelprize.org |year=2014 }}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071118051415/http://www.jameslindlibrary.org/trial_records/19th_Century/vorderman/vorderman_commentary.html Adolphe Vorderman's 1897 study of beriberi among prison inmates in the Dutch East Indies ]\n*[http://ag-vorderman.blogspot.com/ Adolphe Vorderman] by Gercon Vorderman {{dead link|date=August 2014}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vorderman, Adolphe}}\n[[Category:1844 births]]\n[[Category:1902 deaths]]\n[[Category:Dutch physicians]]\n[[Category:Writers from The Hague]]\n[[Category:Members of the Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n", "name_user": "Deb", "label": "safe", "comment": "bring intro into line with bio standards", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolphe_Vorderman"}
{"title_page": "Isai Vellalar", "text_new": "{{Short description|Tamil community traditionally involved in the arts of music and dance.}}\n'''Isai Vellalar''' is a community found in the [[India|Indian]] state of [[Tamil Nadu]]. They are traditionally involved as performers of classical dance and music in [[Hindu temple|Hindu temples]] and [[Court|courts]] of the patrons.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|title=Historical Dictionary of the Tamils|last=University|first=Vijaya Ramaswamy, Jawaharlal Nehru|date=2017-08-25|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|year=|isbn=9781538106860|location=|pages=114\u2013115, 161\u2013162|language=en}}</ref> The term \"Isai Vellalar\" is a recent community identity, and people of [[minstrel]] occupation from various castes such as [[Agamudayar]], Melakkarar, Nanayakkarar, Nattuvanar, [[Sengunthar]] and come under this term.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Of Property and Propriety: The Role of Gender and Class in Imperialism and Nationalism|last=Bannerji|first=Himani|last2=Mojab|first2=Shahrzad|last3=Whitehead|first3=Judith|date=2001|publisher=University of Toronto Press|year=|isbn=9780802081926|location=|pages=162|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|title=Madras Studios: Narrative, Genre, and Ideology in Tamil Cinema|last=Pillai|first=Swarnavel Eswaran|date=2015-01-27|publisher=SAGE Publications India|year=|isbn=9789351502128|location=|pages=231|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe females of this community were occupied as [[Devadasi]] (ritual temple dancers), while the male were occupied as musicians associated with the [[nadaswaram]] (windpipe instrument) and the [[melam]] (drum).<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Etymology ==\nThe term Isai Vellalar derives from the Tamil words ''Isai'' meaning \"music\" and ''[[Vellalar]]'' a generic term roughly meaning \"cultivator\", thus translates as \"cultivators of music\".<ref name=\":0\" /> This term was introduced after the legal abolition of the [[Devadasi]] system as a result of the reform and anti-[[nautch]] movement in 1947.<ref name=\":1\" /> The term \"devadasi\" is a [[Sanskritisation|Sanskritized]] form of the Tamil term ''tevaratiy\u0101l'' (''tevaratiyar'' in plural form) derived from ''thevar'' meaning \"god\" and ''atiyal'' meaning \"female devotee\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite book|title=Donors, Devotees, and Daughters of God: Temple Women in Medieval Tamilnadu|last=Orr|first=Leslie C.|date=2000-03-09|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=|isbn=9780195356724|location=|pages=5, 52, 56|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe Isai Vellalar communities were originally [[Nomad|nomads]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Kalabhras in the Pandiya country and their impact on the life and letters there|last=Arunachalam|first=M.|date=1979|publisher=University of Madras|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=90|language=en}}</ref> [[Bard|Bardic]] traditions are referred in early [[Sangam literature]] and well into the early [[Pallava dynasty|Pallava]] and [[Pandya dynasty|Pandya]] periods. These were primarily ritualistic and defensive in nature. The artistic side of music and dance came to be strengthened during the [[Chola dynasty|Chola]] and [[Vijayanagara Empire|Vijayanagara]] periods, where these elements were observed in the courts and temples.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Other Half of the Coconut: Women Writing Self-respect History : an Anthology of Self-respect Literature (1928-1936)|last=Srilata|first=K.|date=2003|publisher=[[Kali for Women]]|year=|isbn=9788186706503|location=|pages=94|language=en}}</ref>\n\nEarly [[Chola dynasty|Chola]] inscriptions mentions Tevaratiyar as recipients of food offering and ritual performers of the temples, and was a term carrying honorific and high connotations.<ref name=\":2\" /> Inscriptional evidences indicates the Tevaratiyar women to have been independent professionals who enjoyed property (made large land donations to temples) and a respectable position in the society. The 11th-century inscription of [[Rajaraja I]] states that the Tevaratiyar were invited to serve the [[Brihadisvara Temple, Thanjavur|Brihadisvara Temple]] and were given land near the temple.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite book|title=Approaches to History: Essays in Indian Historiography|last=Bhattacharya|first=Sabyasachi|date=2011|publisher=Indian Council of Historical Research (ICHR)|year=|isbn=9789380607177|location=|pages=206|language=en}}</ref>\n\nUnder the patronage of the [[Nayaks of Tanjavur]] and [[Thanjavur Maratha kingdom|Thanjavur Maratha]] kings, [[Telugu people|Telugu]] musicians from [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Maharashtra]] migrated to the [[Thanjavur district|Thanjavur region]]. The Melakkarars of Thanjavur are therefore divided in two distinct linguistic groups \u2013 the Tamil and Telugu Melakkarar.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nWith the entry of [[Colonial India]], great loss of temple patronage resulted the Tevaratiyar to perceive other ways of income which degraded their social status.<ref name=\":3\" /> The [[Devadasi]] system was legally abolished in 1947 after the campaigns of the social reformers [[Moovalur Ramamirtham]] and [[Muthulakshmi Reddi]]. The entry of [[Tamil Brahmin|Tamil Brahmins]] in music and dance was seen as a threat to the traditional performers of these art forms. This led communities traditionally associated with music and dance to start forming a politicized non-Brahmin caste association which they coined as \"Isai Vellalar Sangam\" and thereby created a political unified identity.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== List of famous Isai Vellalars==\n\n===Historical personalities===\n*[[Arunagirinathar]]\n*[[Muthu Thandavar]]\n\n===Social activists===\n*[[Moovalur Ramamirtham]]\n\n===Politicians===\n*[[M Karunanidhi]]\n*[[Murasoli Maran]]\n*[[S. S. Thennarasu]]\n*[[MK Azhagiri]]\n*[[MK Stalin]]\n*[[Kanimozhi]]\n*[[Dayanidhi Maran]]\n\n===Business personalities===\n*[[Kalanithi Maran]]\n\n===Arts===\n*[[T. N. Rajarathnam Pillai]]\n*Thiruveezhimizhalai Brothers Padmashree.  S.Subramania pillai and S.Nataraja Sundaram pillai\n*Thiruveezhimizhalai Brothers S.Govindaraj pillai and Padmashree.S.Dhakshinamoorthy pillai\n*[[Kumbakonam Rajamanickam Pillai]]\n*[[Veenai Dhanammal]]\n*[[P. R. Thilagam]]\n*[[T. K. Swaminatha Pillai]]\n*[[Namagiripettai Krishnan]]\n*[[Thiruvarur Bakthavathsalam]]\n*[[S. Somasundaram]]\n*\n\n===Cinema===\n*[[T. R. Rajakumari]]\n*[[T. S. Balaiah]]\n*[[T. A. Madhuram]]\n*[[AVM Rajan]]\n*[[Junior Balaiah]]\n*[[Manochithra]]\n*[[Thyagu (actor)|Thyagu]]\nUdhaynithi Stalin\n*[[Arulnithi]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n[[Category:Social groups of Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Indian castes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Tamil community traditionally involved in the arts of music and dance.}}\n'''Isai Vellalar''' is a community found in the [[India|Indian]] state of [[Tamil Nadu]]. They are traditionally involved as performers of classical dance and music in [[Hindu temple|Hindu temples]] and [[Court|courts]] of the patrons.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|title=Historical Dictionary of the Tamils|last=University|first=Vijaya Ramaswamy, Jawaharlal Nehru|date=2017-08-25|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|year=|isbn=9781538106860|location=|pages=114\u2013115, 161\u2013162|language=en}}</ref> The term \"Isai Vellalar\" is a recent community identity, and people of [[minstrel]] occupation from various castes such as [[Agamudayar]], Melakkarar, Nanayakkarar, Nattuvanar, [[Sengunthar]] and [[Vellalar]] come under this term.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Of Property and Propriety: The Role of Gender and Class in Imperialism and Nationalism|last=Bannerji|first=Himani|last2=Mojab|first2=Shahrzad|last3=Whitehead|first3=Judith|date=2001|publisher=University of Toronto Press|year=|isbn=9780802081926|location=|pages=162|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|title=Madras Studios: Narrative, Genre, and Ideology in Tamil Cinema|last=Pillai|first=Swarnavel Eswaran|date=2015-01-27|publisher=SAGE Publications India|year=|isbn=9789351502128|location=|pages=231|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe females of this community were occupied as [[Devadasi]] (ritual temple dancers), while the male were occupied as musicians associated with the [[nadaswaram]] (windpipe instrument) and the [[melam]] (drum).<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Etymology ==\nThe term Isai Vellalar derives from the Tamil words ''Isai'' meaning \"music\" and ''[[Vellalar]]'' a generic term roughly meaning \"cultivator\", thus translates as \"cultivators of music\".<ref name=\":0\" /> This term was introduced after the legal abolition of the [[Devadasi]] system as a result of the reform and anti-[[nautch]] movement in 1947.<ref name=\":1\" /> The term \"devadasi\" is a [[Sanskritisation|Sanskritized]] form of the Tamil term ''tevaratiy\u0101l'' (''tevaratiyar'' in plural form) derived from ''thevar'' meaning \"god\" and ''atiyal'' meaning \"female devotee\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite book|title=Donors, Devotees, and Daughters of God: Temple Women in Medieval Tamilnadu|last=Orr|first=Leslie C.|date=2000-03-09|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=|isbn=9780195356724|location=|pages=5, 52, 56|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe Isai Vellalar communities were originally [[Nomad|nomads]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Kalabhras in the Pandiya country and their impact on the life and letters there|last=Arunachalam|first=M.|date=1979|publisher=University of Madras|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=90|language=en}}</ref> [[Bard|Bardic]] traditions are referred in early [[Sangam literature]] and well into the early [[Pallava dynasty|Pallava]] and [[Pandya dynasty|Pandya]] periods. These were primarily ritualistic and defensive in nature. The artistic side of music and dance came to be strengthened during the [[Chola dynasty|Chola]] and [[Vijayanagara Empire|Vijayanagara]] periods, where these elements were observed in the courts and temples.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Other Half of the Coconut: Women Writing Self-respect History : an Anthology of Self-respect Literature (1928-1936)|last=Srilata|first=K.|date=2003|publisher=[[Kali for Women]]|year=|isbn=9788186706503|location=|pages=94|language=en}}</ref>\n\nEarly [[Chola dynasty|Chola]] inscriptions mentions Tevaratiyar as recipients of food offering and ritual performers of the temples, and was a term carrying honorific and high connotations.<ref name=\":2\" /> Inscriptional evidences indicates the Tevaratiyar women to have been independent professionals who enjoyed property (made large land donations to temples) and a respectable position in the society. The 11th-century inscription of [[Rajaraja I]] states that the Tevaratiyar were invited to serve the [[Brihadisvara Temple, Thanjavur|Brihadisvara Temple]] and were given land near the temple.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite book|title=Approaches to History: Essays in Indian Historiography|last=Bhattacharya|first=Sabyasachi|date=2011|publisher=Indian Council of Historical Research (ICHR)|year=|isbn=9789380607177|location=|pages=206|language=en}}</ref>\n\nUnder the patronage of the [[Nayaks of Tanjavur]] and [[Thanjavur Maratha kingdom|Thanjavur Maratha]] kings, [[Telugu people|Telugu]] musicians from [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Maharashtra]] migrated to the [[Thanjavur district|Thanjavur region]]. The Melakkarars of Thanjavur are therefore divided in two distinct linguistic groups \u2013 the Tamil and Telugu Melakkarar.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nWith the entry of [[Colonial India]], great loss of temple patronage resulted the Tevaratiyar to perceive other ways of income which degraded their social status.<ref name=\":3\" /> The [[Devadasi]] system was legally abolished in 1947 after the campaigns of the social reformers [[Moovalur Ramamirtham]] and [[Muthulakshmi Reddi]]. The entry of [[Tamil Brahmin|Tamil Brahmins]] in music and dance was seen as a threat to the traditional performers of these art forms. This led communities traditionally associated with music and dance to start forming a politicized non-Brahmin caste association which they coined as \"Isai Vellalar Sangam\" and thereby created a political unified identity.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== List of famous Isai Vellalars==\n\n===Historical personalities===\n*[[Arunagirinathar]]\n*[[Muthu Thandavar]]\n\n===Social activists===\n*[[Moovalur Ramamirtham]]\n\n===Politicians===\n*[[M Karunanidhi]]\n*[[Murasoli Maran]]\n*[[S. S. Thennarasu]]\n*[[MK Azhagiri]]\n*[[MK Stalin]]\n*[[Kanimozhi]]\n*[[Dayanidhi Maran]]\n\n===Business personalities===\n*[[Kalanithi Maran]]\n\n===Arts===\n*[[T. N. Rajarathnam Pillai]]\n*Thiruveezhimizhalai Brothers Padmashree.  S.Subramania pillai and S.Nataraja Sundaram pillai\n*Thiruveezhimizhalai Brothers S.Govindaraj pillai and Padmashree.S.Dhakshinamoorthy pillai\n*[[Kumbakonam Rajamanickam Pillai]]\n*[[Veenai Dhanammal]]\n*[[P. R. Thilagam]]\n*[[T. K. Swaminatha Pillai]]\n*[[Namagiripettai Krishnan]]\n*[[Thiruvarur Bakthavathsalam]]\n*[[S. Somasundaram]]\n*\n\n===Cinema===\n*[[T. R. Rajakumari]]\n*[[T. S. Balaiah]]\n*[[T. A. Madhuram]]\n*[[AVM Rajan]]\n*[[Junior Balaiah]]\n*[[Manochithra]]\n*[[Thyagu (actor)|Thyagu]]\nUdhaynithi Stalin\n*[[Arulnithi]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n[[Category:Social groups of Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Indian castes]]\n", "name_user": "2601:192:4c7f:c01a:d434:6f96:2501:8129", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isai_Vellalar"}
{"title_page": "Filip Albrecht", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Filip Albrecht\n| image        = Filip Albrecht Letohrad 2012.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| caption      = Filip Albrecht (2012)\n| birth_name   = Hanns Philipp Albrecht\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1977|11|28}}\n| birth_place  = [[Munich]], Germany\n| nationality  = German\n| occupation   = lyricist, manager, producer, film distributor, TV host, writer \n| years_active = 1999\u2013present \n}}\n'''Filip Albrecht''' (born November 28, 1977) is a [[Czechs|Czech]]-German lyricist, manager, producer, film distributor, TV host and writer.\n\n== Life and career==\n[[File:Filip Albrecht, Karl Markovics, Peter Kovar\u010d\u00edk and Gedeon Burkhard 2014.jpg|thumb|right|Filip Albrecht, [[Karl Markovics]], Peter Kov\u00e1r\u010d\u00edk and [[Gedeon Burkhard]] at ''The Devil's Mistress'' press conference in Prague, 2015]]\nBorn in [[Munich]], Albrecht grew up in [[Bavaria]]. In 1999 he decided to move to [[Prague]] and to found a media company to distribute Czech movies all over the world.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kultura.idnes.cz/hudba.aspx?c=A040407_105931_hudba_jup|title=Karel Gott je mu\u017e dvou tv\u00e1\u0159\u00ed|publisher=[[Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES]]|date=April 7, 2004|accessdate=December 6, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001 he began to work as the German lyricist for the two international most successful Czech singers, [[Karel Gott]] and [[Helena Vondr\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1]], writing for them from 2001 to 2017 over 30 songs such as ''Jede Nacht'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://hitparade.ch/song/Karel-Gott/Jede-Nacht-170428|title=Swiss Music Charts (song: Jede Nacht)|publisher=hitparade.ch|date=2003|accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> ''Das Lachen meiner Kinder'' or ''Schau nach vorn'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.universal-music.de/karel-gott/news/detail/article:230500/alle-infos-zum-neuen-album-herr-gott-nochmal-von-karel-gott|title=Press release from Universal Music Group Germany|publisher=universal-music.de|date=October 16, 2014|accessdate=November 20, 2014}}</ref> which were released mainly in the German market ([[Universal Music Group]] Germany, [[Electrola]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/vase-zpravy/praha/3440-22488-textu-pro-karla-gotta-jsem-napsal-asi-dvacet-rika-nemecky-textar-filip-albrecht.html|title=Text\u016f pro Karla Gotta jsem napsal asi dvacet \u0159\u00edk\u00e1 n\u011bmeck\u00fd texta\u0159 Filip Albrecht|publisher=[[Pr\u00e1vo]]|date=January 31, 2014|accessdate=March 26, 2014}}</ref> Since 2003 he is Vondr\u00e1\u010dkova's producer and manager for Germany, [[Austria]] and [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kultura.idnes.cz/vondrackova-uvedla-nemeckou-show-dq8-/filmvideo.aspx?c=A040503_091004_filmvideo_kot|title=Vondr\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1 uvedla n\u011bmeckou show|publisher=[[Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES]]|date=May 3, 2004|accessdate=July 17, 2008}}</ref> Albrecht is also the manager of legendary Czech actor and entertainer Pavel Tr\u00e1vn\u00ed\u010dek ([[Three Nuts for Cinderella]]).\n\nIn 2002 he started his cooperation with the [[Zl\u00edn Film Festival]] being named the Head of International Relations by Czech [[culture minister]] V\u00edt\u011b\u017eslav Jand\u00e1k, and afterwards also with the [[Febiofest]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radio.cz/de/rubrik/kultur/deutsch-tschechische-beziehungen-im-bereich-des-films|title=Deutsch-tschechische Beziehungen im Bereich des Films|publisher=[[\u010cesk\u00fd Rozhlas]]|date=August 17, 2003|accessdate=January 11, 2009}}</ref> From 2002\u20132015 he brought to the [[Czech Republic]] dozens of film personalities like [[Peter Ustinov]], [[J\u00fcrgen Prochnow]], [[Helmut Berger]], [[Maximilian Schell]], [[Pierre Brice]], [[Ottfried Fischer]], [[Hanna Schygulla]], [[Dani Levy]], [[Gojko Miti\u0107]], [[Frank Beyer]], [[G\u00f6tz George]] or [[Armin Mueller-Stahl]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/zhave-drby/38719/vinnetou-brice-chce-tocit-v-cesku.html|title=Vinnetou Brice chce to\u010dit v \u010cesku|publisher=[[Aha! (tabloid)|Aha!]] (czech daily newspaper)|date=September 9, 2009|accessdate=March 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zlinfest.cz/cs/2004/aktuality?id=20|title=O\u010dek\u00e1v\u00e1me zvu\u010dn\u00e1 jm\u00e9na \u2013 Stars of the Festival interviev|publisher=ZLINFEST.cz|date=April 24, 2004|accessdate=August 9, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130429024750/http://www.zlinfest.cz/cs/2004/aktuality?id=20|archivedate=April 29, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> As a [[librettist]] he wrote the German version of the fairy tale ''T\u0159i brat\u0159i'' (\"Three Brothers\"), directed by [[Academy Award]] winner [[Jan Sv\u011br\u00e1k]], and the [[ice show]] ''Aschenputtel on Ice''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/vase-zpravy/praha/3440-22496-sverak-senior-a-sverak-junior-jsou-pro-me-svetova-extratrida-tvrdi-filip-albrecht.html|title=Sv\u011b\u0159\u00e1k junior a Sv\u011br\u00e1k senior jsou pro m\u011b sv\u011btov\u00e1 extrat\u0159\u00edda|publisher=[[Novinky.cz]]|date=February 1, 2014|accessdate=December 20, 2014}}</ref>\n \nSince 2013 Albrecht is the [[programme director]] and vice president of the popular Czech television channels ''\u0160l\u00e1gr TV'' and ''Country Nr.1''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ceskobudejovicky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/pro-ceske-umelce-pise-nemecke-texty-rika-ze-hudba-lidi-spojuje-20140913.html|title=Pro \u010desk\u00e9 um\u011blce p\u00ed\u0161e n\u011bmeck\u00e9 texty \u2013 interviev about \u0160l\u00e1gr TV and Country Nr.1|publisher=[[Den\u00edk]]|date=September 13, 2014|accessdate=September 16, 2014}}</ref> He is the co-author and [[ghostwriter]] of Karel Gott's autobiography ''Zwischen zwei Welten'' (\"Between Two Worlds\"), which was released in Germany in May 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2014/21/karel-gott|title=Die Heiterkeit des Seins|publisher=[[Die Zeit]]|date=May 24, 2014|accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/vase-zpravy/zahranici/nemecko/3440-28247-karel-gott-napsal-letos-pro-nemecky-trh-autobiografii-ktera-se-stala-bestsellerem.html|title=Karel Gott letos napsal autobiografii, kter\u00e1 se stala bestsellerem|publisher=[[Novinky.cz]]|date=November 23, 2014|accessdate=December 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/zhave-drby/96348/karel-gott-oslavi-75-narozeniny-prekvapeni-od-ivanky-ho-dostane.html|title=Karel Gott oslav\u00ed narozeniny, p\u0159ekvapen\u00ed v\u00e1s dostane|publisher=[[Aha! (tabloid)|Aha!]] daily newspaper|date=April 11, 2014|accessdate=April 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAlbrecht hosts the Czech-[[Slovakia|Slovak]] television show ''Se \u0160l\u00e1grem na cest\u00e1ch'' (\"With Music on the Road\")<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|title=ADS-Medienpreis Fernsehen Ausland 2014 f\u00fcr Filip Albrecht!|publisher=Smago (Das Online-Magazin f\u00fcr deutsche Musik)|date=November 26, 2014|accessdate=November 28, 2014|archive-url=https://archive.is/20141227014457/http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|archive-date=December 27, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and appears on several celebrity talkshows.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://programm.orf.at/?story=30533|title=TV announcement by Austrian state television ORF of the VERA show with guests Karel Gott, Filip Albrecht and Ralph Siegel|publisher=[[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]]|date=June 7, 2014|accessdate=October 28, 2014}}</ref> For his work as an \"ambassador\" of Czech music and television shows he was honoured in the ''Smago Award 2014'' ceremony with the ''ADS Medienpreis'' by the ''Arbeitsgemeinschaft Deutscher Schlager & Volksmusik'' e.v. in [[Berlin]] in November 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|title=ADS-Medienpreis Fernsehen Ausland 2014 f\u00fcr Filip Albrecht!|publisher=Smago (Das Online-Magazin f\u00fcr deutsche Musik)|date=November 26, 2014|accessdate=November 28, 2014|archive-url=https://archive.is/20141227014457/http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|archive-date=December 27, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68671/|title=Die \"smago! Award 2014\" Preistr\u00e4ger(innen) in der \u00dcbersicht!|publisher=Smago (Das Online-Magazin f\u00fcr deutsche Musik)|date=November 28, 2014|accessdate=April 23, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141201045747/http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68671/|archive-date=December 1, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe is the coproducer of the biographical film movie ''The Devil's Mistress'' (director: [[Filip Ren\u010d]]) about the life of Czech actress [[L\u00edda Baarov\u00e1]] and her affair with [[Joseph Goebbels]] starring [[Karl Markovics]], [[Gedeon Burkhard]] and [[Tatiana Pauhofova]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/filip-renc-zacne-film-o-baarove-tocit-v-breznu/1176904|title=Filip Ren\u010d za\u010dne film o Baarov\u00e9 to\u010dit v b\u0159eznu|publisher=[[\u010cTK]]|date=February 3, 2015|accessdate=February 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://diepresse.com/home/kultur/film/4633743/Karl-Markovics-spielt-Joseph-Goebbels|title=Karl Markovics spielt Joseph Goebbels|publisher=[[Die Presse]]|date=January 8, 2015|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> World premiere was in January 2016 in Prague under the attendance of Czech president [[Milo\u0161 Zeman]].\n\nIn October 2016 he was named the Festival Director of the first European Fairy Tale Film Festival ''Internationales M\u00e4rchenfilmfestival Fabulix'' in [[Annaberg-Buchholz]] ([[Saxony]]). Albrecht is a founding member of the festival.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tag24.de/nachrichten/annaberg-buchholz-maerchenhaftes-festival-filmfest-stadt-ries-fabulix-sommer-228723|title=Ries-Stadt feiert mit vielen Stars m\u00e4rchenhaftes Filmfest|publisher=[[Morgenpost.de]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mdr.de/sachsen/chemnitz/annaberg-buchholz-stellt-maerchenfilmfestival-fabulix-vor-100.html|title=Fabulix zaubert Sommerm\u00e4rchen nach Annaberg-Buchholz|publisher=[[Mitteldeutscher Rundfunk|MDR]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=June 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328031542/http://www.mdr.de/sachsen/chemnitz/annaberg-buchholz-stellt-maerchenfilmfestival-fabulix-vor-100.html|archive-date=March 28, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.freiepresse.de/LOKALES/ERZGEBIRGE/SCHWARZENBERG/Echtes-Prinzenpaar-kommt-zu-Fabulix-artikel9860606.php|title=Echtes Prinzenpaar kommt zu Fabulix|publisher=[[Freie Presse (Saxony)|Freie Presse]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref> The first edition of the festival (2017) took place from August 23 to the 27th, and was visited by over 20.000 guests.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/regionales/sachsen/article168033319/Rund-20-000-Besucher-bei-Maerchenfilm-Festival-fabulix.html|title=Rund 20.000 Besucher bei M\u00e4rchenfilm-Festival \"fabulix\"|publisher=[[Die Welt]]|date=August 27, 2017|accessdate=October 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlbrecht is a member of the [[Rotary Club]] Prague International.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rotary2240.org/prague-international/cs/seznam-clenu/|title=Seznam \u010dlenu RC Prague International|publisher=Rotary International|date=November 10, 2016|accessdate=November 11, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113033020/https://www.rotary2240.org/prague-international/cs/seznam-clenu//|archive-date=November 13, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe lives in Prague and in [[Nice]].\n\n==References==\n[[File:Filip_Albrecht_bei_der_Closing_Gala_des_Festivals_Fabulix.jpg|thumb|right|Albrecht presenting the Closing Gala of the ''Fabulix'' Film Festival, 2017]]\n[[File:Filip Albrecht at the Broadway Dr.Zhivago premiere, April 2015.jpg|thumb|right|Filip Albrecht at the Broadway premiere of ''Doctor Zhivago'', 2015]]\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Filip Albrecht}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Albrecht, Filip}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Czech television personalities]]\n[[Category:German lyricists]]\n[[Category:Czech male writers]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n[[Category:German emigrants to the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:People from Prague]]\n[[Category:Writers from Prague]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Filip Albrecht\n| image        = Filip Albrecht Letohrad 2012.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| caption      = Filip Albrecht (2012)\n| birth_name   = Hanns Philipp Albrecht\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1977|11|28}}\n| birth_place  = [[Munich]], Germany\n| nationality  = German\n| occupation   = lyricist, manager, producer, film distributor, TV host, writer \n| years_active = 1999\u2013present \n}}\n'''Filip Albrecht''' (born November 28, 1977) is a [[Czechs|Czech]]-German lyricist, manager, producer, film distributor, TV host and writer.\n\n== Life and career==\n[[File:Filip Albrecht, Karl Markovics, Peter Kovar\u010d\u00edk and Gedeon Burkhard 2014.jpg|thumb|right|Filip Albrecht, [[Karl Markovics]], Peter Kov\u00e1r\u010d\u00edk and [[Gedeon Burkhard]] at ''The Devil's Mistress'' press conference in Prague, 2015]]\nBorn in [[Munich]], Albrecht grew up in [[Bavaria]]. In 1999 he decided to move to [[Prague]] and to found a media company to distribute Czech movies all over the world.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kultura.idnes.cz/hudba.aspx?c=A040407_105931_hudba_jup|title=Karel Gott je mu\u017e dvou tv\u00e1\u0159\u00ed|publisher=[[Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES]]|date=April 7, 2004|accessdate=December 6, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001 he began to work as the German lyricist for the two international most successful Czech singers, [[Karel Gott]] and [[Helena Vondr\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1]], writing for them from 2001 to 2017 over 30 songs such as ''Jede Nacht'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://hitparade.ch/song/Karel-Gott/Jede-Nacht-170428|title=Swiss Music Charts (song: Jede Nacht)|publisher=hitparade.ch|date=2003|accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> ''Das Lachen meiner Kinder'' or ''Schau nach vorn'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.universal-music.de/karel-gott/news/detail/article:230500/alle-infos-zum-neuen-album-herr-gott-nochmal-von-karel-gott|title=Press release from Universal Music Group Germany|publisher=universal-music.de|date=October 16, 2014|accessdate=November 20, 2014}}</ref> which were released mainly in the German market ([[Universal Music Group]] Germany, [[Electrola]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/vase-zpravy/praha/3440-22488-textu-pro-karla-gotta-jsem-napsal-asi-dvacet-rika-nemecky-textar-filip-albrecht.html|title=Text\u016f pro Karla Gotta jsem napsal asi dvacet \u0159\u00edk\u00e1 n\u011bmeck\u00fd texta\u0159 Filip Albrecht|publisher=[[Pr\u00e1vo]]|date=January 31, 2014|accessdate=March 26, 2014}}</ref> Since 2003 he is Vondr\u00e1\u010dkova's producer and manager for Germany, [[Austria]] and [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kultura.idnes.cz/vondrackova-uvedla-nemeckou-show-dq8-/filmvideo.aspx?c=A040503_091004_filmvideo_kot|title=Vondr\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1 uvedla n\u011bmeckou show|publisher=[[Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES]]|date=May 3, 2004|accessdate=July 17, 2008}}</ref> Albrecht is also the manager of legendary Czech actor and entertainer Pavel Tr\u00e1vn\u00ed\u010dek ([[Three Nuts for Cinderella]]).\n\nIn 2002 he started his cooperation with the [[Zl\u00edn Film Festival]] being named the Head of International Relations by Czech [[culture minister]] V\u00edt\u011b\u017eslav Jand\u00e1k, and afterwards also with the [[Febiofest]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radio.cz/de/rubrik/kultur/deutsch-tschechische-beziehungen-im-bereich-des-films|title=Deutsch-tschechische Beziehungen im Bereich des Films|publisher=[[\u010cesk\u00fd Rozhlas]]|date=August 17, 2003|accessdate=January 11, 2009}}</ref> From 2002\u20132015 he brought to the [[Czech Republic]] dozens of film personalities like [[Peter Ustinov]], [[J\u00fcrgen Prochnow]], [[Helmut Berger]], [[Maximilian Schell]], [[Pierre Brice]], [[Ottfried Fischer]], [[Hanna Schygulla]], [[Dani Levy]], [[Gojko Miti\u0107]], [[Frank Beyer]], [[G\u00f6tz George]] or [[Armin Mueller-Stahl]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/zhave-drby/38719/vinnetou-brice-chce-tocit-v-cesku.html|title=Vinnetou Brice chce to\u010dit v \u010cesku|publisher=[[Aha! (tabloid)|Aha!]] (czech daily newspaper)|date=September 9, 2009|accessdate=March 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zlinfest.cz/cs/2004/aktuality?id=20|title=O\u010dek\u00e1v\u00e1me zvu\u010dn\u00e1 jm\u00e9na \u2013 Stars of the Festival interviev|publisher=ZLINFEST.cz|date=April 24, 2004|accessdate=August 9, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130429024750/http://www.zlinfest.cz/cs/2004/aktuality?id=20|archivedate=April 29, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> As a [[librettist]] he wrote the German version of the fairy tale ''T\u0159i brat\u0159i'' (\"Three Brothers\"), directed by [[Academy Award]] winner [[Jan Sv\u011br\u00e1k]], and the [[ice show]] ''Aschenputtel on Ice''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/vase-zpravy/praha/3440-22496-sverak-senior-a-sverak-junior-jsou-pro-me-svetova-extratrida-tvrdi-filip-albrecht.html|title=Sv\u011b\u0159\u00e1k junior a Sv\u011br\u00e1k senior jsou pro m\u011b sv\u011btov\u00e1 extrat\u0159\u00edda|publisher=[[Novinky.cz]]|date=February 1, 2014|accessdate=December 20, 2014}}</ref>\n \nSince 2013 Albrecht is the [[programme director]] and vice president of the popular Czech television channels ''\u0160l\u00e1gr TV'' and ''Country Nr.1''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ceskobudejovicky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/pro-ceske-umelce-pise-nemecke-texty-rika-ze-hudba-lidi-spojuje-20140913.html|title=Pro \u010desk\u00e9 um\u011blce p\u00ed\u0161e n\u011bmeck\u00e9 texty \u2013 interviev about \u0160l\u00e1gr TV and Country Nr.1|publisher=[[Den\u00edk]]|date=September 13, 2014|accessdate=September 16, 2014}}</ref> He is the co-author and [[ghostwriter]] of Karel Gott's autobiography ''Zwischen zwei Welten'' (\"Between Two Worlds\"), which was released in Germany in May 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2014/21/karel-gott|title=Die Heiterkeit des Seins|publisher=[[Die Zeit]]|date=May 24, 2014|accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/vase-zpravy/zahranici/nemecko/3440-28247-karel-gott-napsal-letos-pro-nemecky-trh-autobiografii-ktera-se-stala-bestsellerem.html|title=Karel Gott letos napsal autobiografii, kter\u00e1 se stala bestsellerem|publisher=[[Novinky.cz]]|date=November 23, 2014|accessdate=December 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/zhave-drby/96348/karel-gott-oslavi-75-narozeniny-prekvapeni-od-ivanky-ho-dostane.html|title=Karel Gott oslav\u00ed narozeniny, p\u0159ekvapen\u00ed v\u00e1s dostane|publisher=[[Aha! (tabloid)|Aha!]] daily newspaper|date=April 11, 2014|accessdate=April 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAlbrecht hosts the Czech-[[Slovakia|Slovak]] television show ''Se \u0160l\u00e1grem na cest\u00e1ch'' (\"With Music on the Road\")<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|title=ADS-Medienpreis Fernsehen Ausland 2014 f\u00fcr Filip Albrecht!|publisher=Smago (Das Online-Magazin f\u00fcr deutsche Musik)|date=November 26, 2014|accessdate=November 28, 2014|archive-url=https://archive.is/20141227014457/http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|archive-date=December 27, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and appears on several celebrity talkshows.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://programm.orf.at/?story=30533|title=TV announcement by Austrian state television ORF of the VERA show with guests Karel Gott, Filip Albrecht and Ralph Siegel|publisher=[[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]]|date=June 7, 2014|accessdate=October 28, 2014}}</ref> For his work as an \"ambassador\" of Czech music and television shows he was honoured in the ''Smago Award 2014'' ceremony with the ''ADS Medienpreis'' by the ''Arbeitsgemeinschaft Deutscher Schlager & Volksmusik'' e.v. in [[Berlin]] in November 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|title=ADS-Medienpreis Fernsehen Ausland 2014 f\u00fcr Filip Albrecht!|publisher=Smago (Das Online-Magazin f\u00fcr deutsche Musik)|date=November 26, 2014|accessdate=November 28, 2014|archive-url=https://archive.is/20141227014457/http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68667/|archive-date=December 27, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68671/|title=Die \"smago! Award 2014\" Preistr\u00e4ger(innen) in der \u00dcbersicht!|publisher=Smago (Das Online-Magazin f\u00fcr deutsche Musik)|date=November 28, 2014|accessdate=April 23, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141201045747/http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/68671/|archive-date=December 1, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe is the coproducer of the biographical film movie ''The Devil's Mistress'' (director: [[Filip Ren\u010d]]) about the life of Czech actress [[L\u00edda Baarov\u00e1]] and her affair with [[Joseph Goebbels]] starring [[Karl Markovics]], [[Gedeon Burkhard]] and [[Tatiana Pauhofova]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/filip-renc-zacne-film-o-baarove-tocit-v-breznu/1176904|title=Filip Ren\u010d za\u010dne film o Baarov\u00e9 to\u010dit v b\u0159eznu|publisher=[[\u010cTK]]|date=February 3, 2015|accessdate=February 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://diepresse.com/home/kultur/film/4633743/Karl-Markovics-spielt-Joseph-Goebbels|title=Karl Markovics spielt Joseph Goebbels|publisher=[[Die Presse]]|date=January 8, 2015|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> World premiere was in January 2016 in Prague under the attendance of Czech president [[Milo\u0161 Zeman]].\n\nIn October 2016 he was named the Festival Director of the first European Fairy Tale Film Festival ''Internationales M\u00e4rchenfilmfestival Fabulix'' in [[Annaberg-Buchholz]] ([[Saxony]]). Albrecht is a founding member of the festival.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tag24.de/nachrichten/annaberg-buchholz-maerchenhaftes-festival-filmfest-stadt-ries-fabulix-sommer-228723|title=Ries-Stadt feiert mit vielen Stars m\u00e4rchenhaftes Filmfest|publisher=[[Morgenpost.de]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mdr.de/sachsen/chemnitz/annaberg-buchholz-stellt-maerchenfilmfestival-fabulix-vor-100.html|title=Fabulix zaubert Sommerm\u00e4rchen nach Annaberg-Buchholz|publisher=[[Mitteldeutscher Rundfunk|MDR]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=June 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328031542/http://www.mdr.de/sachsen/chemnitz/annaberg-buchholz-stellt-maerchenfilmfestival-fabulix-vor-100.html|archive-date=March 28, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.freiepresse.de/LOKALES/ERZGEBIRGE/SCHWARZENBERG/Echtes-Prinzenpaar-kommt-zu-Fabulix-artikel9860606.php|title=Echtes Prinzenpaar kommt zu Fabulix|publisher=[[Freie Presse (Saxony)|Freie Presse]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref> The first edition of the festival (2017) took place from August 23rd to the 27th, and was visited by over 20.000 guests.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/regionales/sachsen/article168033319/Rund-20-000-Besucher-bei-Maerchenfilm-Festival-fabulix.html|title=Rund 20.000 Besucher bei M\u00e4rchenfilm-Festival \"fabulix\"|publisher=[[Die Welt]]|date=August 27, 2017|accessdate=October 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlbrecht is a member of the [[Rotary Club]] Prague International.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rotary2240.org/prague-international/cs/seznam-clenu/|title=Seznam \u010dlenu RC Prague International|publisher=Rotary International|date=November 10, 2016|accessdate=November 11, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113033020/https://www.rotary2240.org/prague-international/cs/seznam-clenu//|archive-date=November 13, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe lives in Prague and in [[Nice]].\n\n==References==\n[[File:Filip_Albrecht_bei_der_Closing_Gala_des_Festivals_Fabulix.jpg|thumb|right|Albrecht presenting the Closing Gala of the ''Fabulix'' Film Festival, 2017]]\n[[File:Filip Albrecht at the Broadway Dr.Zhivago premiere, April 2015.jpg|thumb|right|Filip Albrecht at the Broadway premiere of ''Doctor Zhivago'', 2015]]\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Filip Albrecht}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Albrecht, Filip}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Czech television personalities]]\n[[Category:German lyricists]]\n[[Category:Czech male writers]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n[[Category:German emigrants to the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:People from Prague]]\n[[Category:Writers from Prague]]\n{{CzechRepublic-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control, removed stub tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Filip_Albrecht"}
{"title_page": "Real Time Crime Center", "text_new": "{{news release|1=article|date=October 2015}}\n[[Image:Realtimecrimecenterofficial.png|thumb|Real Time Crime Center emblem]]\n\nThe '''Real Time Crime Center''' ('''RTCC''') is a centralized technology center for the [[New York Police Department]] (NYPD). Its purpose is to give field officers and detectives instant information to help identify patterns and stop emerging crime. \n\nThe NYPD RTCC opened on July 18, 2005 and provides support 24/7. The center was built at a cost of $11 million. The information in the center is available to the 37,000 police officers of the [[New York City Police Department]].  The RTCC was funded in part by grants from the non-profit [[New York City Police Foundation]].<ref>\n*[http://www.ny1.com/ny1/content/index.jsp?&aid=52142 NYPD Unveils High-Tech Real Time Crime Center At Police Headquarters]\n*[http://www.gcn.com/print/24_29/37061-1.html Real-time crime fighting comes to Gotham]\n</ref>\n\nRTCC data sources include a data warehouse in which billions of records are made available to detectives and other officers within minutes, instead of days or weeks. These include:<ref>\n*[http://policechiefmagazine.org/magazine/index.cfm?fuseaction=display&article_id=995&issue_id=92006 Stopping Crime in Real Time]\n*[http://www.informationweek.com/showArticle.jhtml?articleID=166401859  New York's Techno Crime Fighters]\n*[https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,1895,1863497,00.asp Fighting Crime in Real Time]\n</ref>\n*More than 5 million New York State criminal records, parole and probation files,\n*More than 20 million New York City criminal complaints, arrests, 911/311 calls and summonses spanning five years,\n*More than 31 million national crime records,\n*More than 33 billion public records.\n\nThe Crime Center employs satellite imaging and mapping of New York City (using [[Geographic Information System]] software) precinct-by-precinct. The link analysis capacity of the RTCC can track suspects to their known addresses and point detectives to the locations where they are most likely to flee. The Real Time Crime Center was built with the oversight of integrated solution{{solution-inline|date=July 2019}} provider [[Dimension Data]].\n\nOther police departments have Real Time Crime Centers, including the [[Miami-Dade Police Department]], [[Seattle Police Department]], [[Fort Worth Police Department]], [[Metropolitan Police Department, City of St. Louis]], [[Albuquerque Police Department]], [[Austin Police Department]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kxan.com/news/crime/how-police-monitors-situations-in-downtown-austin-in-realtime_20180316013018707/1049643246|title=How police monitors situations in downtown Austin in realtime|last=Rangel|first=Leslie|date=2016-08-02|work=KXAN|access-date=2018-10-10|language=en-US}}</ref>, [[Tampa Police Department]], [[Minneapolis Police Department]] and [[Houston Police Department|Houston]] Police Departments.<ref>[http://abclocal.go.com/ktrk/story?section=news/in_focus&id=7642890 HPD's High-tech center helping solve crimes]</ref>\n<br />\n<br />\n'''Emerging Technology and Innovation'''\n\nReal Time Crime Center (RTCC) in the Cloud are centralized ([[SaaS]]) platforms which extract and unifies live video and data feeds from virtually any source, creating a central hub that enhances the situational awareness and investigative capabilities of law enforcement and public safety agencies. \n\nOn April 1, 2020, the Minneapolis Police Department's Strategic Information Center (SIC) has announced a partnership with, [https://www.fusus.com/ F\u016bsus], to activate a ground-breaking law enforcement platform, [https://www.fusus.com/products/fususone f\u016bsusONE], on April 16th, 2020.    \n<br />\n<br />\n''\"We\u2019ve worked closely with the Fusus team to help create a real-time crime center solution that truly meets the day-to-day intelligence needs of our department,\u201d said Commander Scott Gerlicher of the MPD\u2019s Special Operation and Intelligence Division. \u201c[https://www.fusus.com/blog/press-release-minneapolis-police-department-to-activate-fusus-real-time-crime-center-platform The activation of the Fusus platform] represents a significant step forward not just for the MPD's crime mitigation and public safety efforts, but for law enforcement technology in general. With the Fusus platform in place, the MPD will be one of the first Police Departments in the nation to be leveraging a real-time crime center in the cloud solution.\u201d''  \n<br />\n<br />\n'''The F\u016bsus Unified Awareness Platform will bring the following capabilities to the MPD\u2019s SIC:''' \n\n*Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) Integration -along with video correlation to Priority 1 locations\n*Integration to Minneapolis 911 dispatch\n*Live video from the Minneapolis Downtown Improvement District area\n*Community Camera Registry Location Data\n*Live Cell Phone Video during an ongoing incident\n*Live Video from Stadiums and other Community Owned Video Sources\n*ShotSpotter Gunfire Detection Integration\n*Mutual Aid with other law enforcement agencies\n*Community shared video and photo for Tips via SMS-Text\n*f\u016bsusALERT Panic App integration for(policy-based) video sharing on alert\n*[https://www.fusus.com/products/fusuops f\u016bsusOPS] Officer Locations, Text Communications,and Team Coordination for Incident Management\n*\u00a0Floor plan Integrations to Locations of Interest\n\n<br />\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.nycpolicefoundation.org/ New York City Police Foundation official site]\n*[https://www.fusus.com/products/fususone F\u016bsus - Real Time Crime Center in the Cloud]\n{{New York City Police Department}}\n[[Category:New York City Police Department]]\n{{police-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{news release|1=article|date=October 2015}}\n[[Image:Realtimecrimecenterofficial.png|thumb|Real Time Crime Center emblem]]\n\nThe '''Real Time Crime Center''' ('''RTCC''') is a centralized technology center for the [[New York Police Department]] (NYPD). Its purpose is to give field officers and detectives instant information to help identify patterns and stop emerging crime. \n\nThe NYPD RTCC opened on July 18, 2005 and provides support 24/7. The center was built at a cost of $11 million. The information in the center is available to the 37,000 police officers of the [[New York City Police Department]].  The RTCC was funded in part by grants from the non-profit [[New York City Police Foundation]].<ref>\n*[http://www.ny1.com/ny1/content/index.jsp?&aid=52142 NYPD Unveils High-Tech Real Time Crime Center At Police Headquarters]\n*[http://www.gcn.com/print/24_29/37061-1.html Real-time crime fighting comes to Gotham]\n</ref>\n\nRTCC data sources include a data warehouse in which billions of records are made available to detectives and other officers within minutes, instead of days or weeks. These include:<ref>\n*[http://policechiefmagazine.org/magazine/index.cfm?fuseaction=display&article_id=995&issue_id=92006 Stopping Crime in Real Time]\n*[http://www.informationweek.com/showArticle.jhtml?articleID=166401859  New York's Techno Crime Fighters]\n*[https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,1895,1863497,00.asp Fighting Crime in Real Time]\n</ref>\n*More than 5 million New York State criminal records, parole and probation files,\n*More than 20 million New York City criminal complaints, arrests, 911/311 calls and summonses spanning five years,\n*More than 31 million national crime records,\n*More than 33 billion public records.\n\nThe Crime Center employs satellite imaging and mapping of New York City (using [[Geographic Information System]] software) precinct-by-precinct. The link analysis capacity of the RTCC can track suspects to their known addresses and point detectives to the locations where they are most likely to flee. The Real Time Crime Center was built with the oversight of integrated solution{{solution-inline|date=July 2019}} provider [[Dimension Data]].\n\nOther police departments have Real Time Crime Centers, including the [[Miami-Dade Police Department]], [[Seattle Police Department]], [[Fort Worth Police Department]], [[Metropolitan Police Department, City of St. Louis]], [[Albuquerque Police Department]], [[Austin Police Department]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kxan.com/news/crime/how-police-monitors-situations-in-downtown-austin-in-realtime_20180316013018707/1049643246|title=How police monitors situations in downtown Austin in realtime|last=Rangel|first=Leslie|date=2016-08-02|work=KXAN|access-date=2018-10-10|language=en-US}}</ref>, [[Tampa Police Department]], [[Minneapolis Police Department]] and [[Houston Police Department|Houston]] Police Departments.<ref>[http://abclocal.go.com/ktrk/story?section=news/in_focus&id=7642890 HPD's High-tech center helping solve crimes]</ref>\n\n'''Emerging Technology and Innovation'''\n\nReal Time Crime Center (RTCC) in the Cloud are centralized ([[SaaS]]) platforms which extract and unifies live video and data feeds from virtually any source, creating a central hub that enhances the situational awareness and investigative capabilities of law enforcement and public safety agencies. \n\nOn April 1, 2020, the Minneapolis Police Department's Strategic Information Center (SIC) has announced a partnership with, [https://www.fusus.com/ F\u016bsus], to activate a ground-breaking law enforcement platform, [https://www.fusus.com/products/fususone f\u016bsusONE], on April 16th, 2020.    \n<br />\n<br />\n''\"We\u2019ve worked closely with the Fusus team to help create a real-time crime center solution that truly meets the day-to-day intelligence needs of our department,\u201d said Commander Scott Gerlicher of the MPD\u2019s Special Operation and Intelligence Division. \u201c[https://www.fusus.com/blog/press-release-minneapolis-police-department-to-activate-fusus-real-time-crime-center-platform The activation of the Fusus platform] represents a significant step forward not just for the MPD's crime mitigation and public safety efforts, but for law enforcement technology in general. With the Fusus platform in place, the MPD will be one of the first Police Departments in the nation to be leveraging a real-time crime center in the cloud solution.\u201d''  \n<br />\n<br />\n'''The F\u016bsus Unified Awareness Platform will bring the following capabilities to the MPD\u2019s SIC:''' \n\n*Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) Integration -along with video correlation to Priority 1 locations\n*Integration to Minneapolis 911 dispatch\n*Live video from the Minneapolis Downtown Improvement District area\n*Community Camera Registry Location Data\n*Live Cell Phone Video during an ongoing incident\n*Live Video from Stadiums and other Community Owned Video Sources\n*ShotSpotter Gunfire Detection Integration\n*Mutual Aid with other law enforcement agencies\n*Community shared video and photo for Tips via SMS-Text\n*f\u016bsusALERT Panic App integration for(policy-based) video sharing on alert\n*[https://www.fusus.com/products/fusuops f\u016bsusOPS] Officer Locations, Text Communications,and Team Coordination for Incident Management\n*\u00a0Floor plan Integrations to Locations of Interest\n\n<br />\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.nycpolicefoundation.org/ New York City Police Foundation official site]\n*[https://www.fusus.com/products/fususone F\u016bsus - Real Time Crime Center in the Cloud]\n{{New York City Police Department}}\n[[Category:New York City Police Department]]\n{{police-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Appleseed1492", "label": "safe", "comment": "spacing edit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_Time_Crime_Center"}
{"title_page": "Mohammad Mobarak Ali", "text_new": "{{short description|Bangladeshi politician}}{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Mohammad Mobarak Ali\n| office              = Member of Bangladesh Parliament\n| term_start          = 1986\n| term_end            = 1990\n| predecessor         = [[Chhattar Bhuiyan]]\n| successor           = [[M. K. Anwar]]\n| birth_date          = \n| birth_place         = \n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = [[Jatiya Party (Ershad)]]\n| bodyclass           = \n| mainwidth           = \n| native_name         = \u09ae\u09cb\u09b9\u09be\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6 \u09ae\u09cb\u09ac\u09be\u09b0\u0995 \u0986\u09b2\u09c0\n| native_name_lang    = bn\n}}\n'''Mohammad Mobarak Ali''' is a [[Jatiya Party (Ershad)]] politician and the former Member of Parliament of [[Comilla-1]].\n\n==Career==\nAli was elected to parliament from [[Comilla-1]] as a Jatiya Party candidate in 1986 and 1988.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"List of 3rd Parliament Members\" |url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/images/pdf/formermp/3rd.pdf |website=parliament.gov.bd |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"List of 4th Parliament Members\" |url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/images/pdf/formermp/4th.pdf |publisher=Bangladesh Parliament (in Bengali). |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ali}}\n[[Category:Jatiya Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:3rd Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:4th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bangladeshi politician}}{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Mohammad Mobarak Ali\n| office = Member of Bangladesh Parliament\n| term_start = \n| term_end = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Jatiya Party (Ershad)]]\n| bodyclass = \n| mainwidth = \n}}\n'''Mohammad Mobarak Ali''' is a [[Jatiya Party (Ershad)]] politician and the former Member of Parliament of [[Comilla-1]].\n\n==Career==\nAli was elected to parliament from Comilla-1 as a Jatiya Party candidate in 1986 and 1988.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"List of 3rd Parliament Members\" |url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/images/pdf/formermp/3rd.pdf |website=parliament.gov.bd |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"List of 4th Parliament Members\" |url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/images/pdf/formermp/4th.pdf |publisher=Bangladesh Parliament (in Bengali). |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ali}}\n[[Category:Jatiya Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:3rd Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:4th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Nabil", "label": "safe", "comment": "Expanding article", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohammad_Mobarak_Ali"}
{"title_page": "South India Saiva Siddhanta Works Publishing Society Ltd.", "text_new": "The South India Saiva Siddhanta Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd. was founded in the year 1920 and started its function from [[Tirunelveli]]. Thiru. V. Thiruvarangam Pillai and Nellai Tamil saivites formed this company to publish books on Tamil and Saiva Samayam.  Thiru. V. Thiruvarangam Pillai had good contact with Maraimalai Adigal who was also a great saivite lecturer. [[Maraimalai Adigal]] was an English professor at Madras Christian College, Tambaram. The Madras operation was taken care by Thiru V.Subbiah Pillai.<br>\n\nFollowing the death of Thiru V. Thiruvarangam Pillai (1944), Thiru. V. Subbiah Pillai took over the administration as Managing Director of the company until 1983. Thiru V. Thiruvarangam Pillai published so many rare Tamil books and have contributed much to the Tamil book world. He took immense interest and brought into the book form by publishing all the lectures disclosed by Maraimalai Adigal, at Colombo, Sri Lanka.\nThe South India Saiva Siddhanta Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd., formed a library called Maraimalai adigal Library at Linghi Street, Madras George Town area. Thiru V. Subbiah Pillai took much interest in forming this library. Thiru. R. Muthukumaraswamy was the Librarian in-charge. \nThiru V. Kalyana Sundaram who was the General Manager of The South India Saiva Siddhanta Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd., has contributed much to the Tamil book industry. He who coined the name Pavazha Vizha in Tamil for 75th Birthday celebration.<br>\n\nIn 1969, Thiru V. Subbiah Pillai for Literature & Education Service was honoured by the Indian Government with Padma Shri. He was keen in translating in pure Tamil, the same was named as Thamarai Chelvar and he was called as Thamarai Chelvar V. Subbiah Pillai.\nAfter the demise of Padma Shri V.Subbiah Pillai R.Muthukumaraswamy took charge as MD of Kazhagam. He was the conference secretary of the 5th International Tamil Conference which was held at Madurai Kamaraj University, Madurai under the able leadership of then Chief Minister Dr.MGR and he was the souvenir committee member of the 2nd International Tamil Conference which was held at Madras which was conducted by our then Chief Minister Thiru. C.N. Annadurai. Thiru R.Muthukumaraswamy was the President of BAPASI, The Booksellers' & Publishers' Association of South India Chennai Book Fair in the year 2004 \u2013 2005[1]<br>\n\nThe company has published books on Tamil Sangam Literature, Tirukkural Thelivurai by Mu.Va., Kazhaga Tamil Dictionary, Kazhaga Tamil English Dictionary, Kazhaga English Tamil Dictionary, Thirumanthiram with Ramanatha Pulavar Prose, Thiruvasagam with Ramanatha Pulavar Prose, etc. Works by Devaneya Pavanar and M. S. Purnalingam Pillai have also been published through this publishing house. The most famous title of this publishing house is Thirukkural Thelivurai written by a great Tamil Scholar Mu. Varadarajan.\nThe Kazhagam is now entering 100th year of celebration.\n\nRecognition\nIn 1969, Sri V. Subbiah Pillai for Literature & Education Service was honoured by the Indian Government with [[Padma Shri Awards (1960\u20131969)]].\n\n\n{{unreferenced|date=August 2017}}\n{{notability|date=August 2017}}\n'''The South India Saiva Siddhantha Works Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd.''' (also known as '''Kazhagam''') is a Tamil book publishing company.\n\n== Books published ==\n* Cattanar's [[Manimekalai]] - P. Pandian (Bacon), Manimekalai translated from the Tamil in English, Madras: South India Saiva Siddhanta Works Publishing Society Ltd., 1989\n* Thirukural Thelivurai Mu.Varadarajanar \n* Nalvar Varalaru\n* Kazhagam Tamil English Dictionary\n* Kazhagam Tamil Purananooru Tamil Ilakanam\n* Kazhagam Senthamil Selvi - Monthly Magazine\n* Kazhagam Tamil Agarathi\n* Kazhagam Tamil Ilakkanam\n* Kazhagam Tamil Vina Vidai\n* Thirumanthiram prose by Pulavar Ramanatha Pillai\n* Thiruvasagam prose by Pulavar Ramanatha Pillai\n* Thirukkovaiyar puthiya vilakkavuraiyudan\n* 63 Nayanmargal Varalaru\n* Sanga Ilakkiyam (Muzhimaiyuma Uraiyudan)\n* Ettu Thogai\n* Pathu Paattu\n* Pathinen Keezhkanakku\n* Sillapathikaram prose by Po. Ve Somasundaranar\n* Manimegalai with Prose\n* Tholkappiyam Ezhuthu Sol Porul\n* Thiruppugazh with Chengalvaraya Pillai Prose\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Book publishing companies of India]]\n", "text_old": "The South India Saiva Siddhanta Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd. was founded in the year 1920 and started its function from [[Tirunelveli]]. Thiru. V. Thiruvarangam Pillai and Nellai Tamil saivites formed this company to publish books on Tamil and Saiva Samayam.  Thiru. V. Thiruvarangam Pillai had good contact with Maraimalai Adigal who was also a great saivite lecturer. [[Maraimalai Adigal]] was an English professor at Madras Christian College, Tambaram. The Madras operation was taken care by Thiru V.Subbiah Pillai.<br>\n\nFollowing the death of Thiru V. Thiruvarangam Pillai (1944), Thiru. V. Subbiah Pillai took over the administration as Managing Director of the company until 1983. Thiru V. Thiruvarangam Pillai published so many rare tamil books and have contributed much to the Tamil book world. He took immense interest and brought into the book form by publishing all the lectures disclosed by Maraimalai Adigal, at Colombo, Sri Lanka.\nThe South India Saiva Siddhanta Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd., formed a library called Maraimalai adigal Library at Linghi Street, Madras George Town area. Thiru V. Subbiah Pillai took much interest in forming this library. Thiru. R. Muthukumaraswamy was the Librarian in-charge. \nThiru V. Kalyana Sundaram who was the General Manager of The South India Saiva Siddhanta Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd., has contributed much to the Tamil book industry. He who coined the name Pavazha Vizha in Tamil for 75th Birthday celebration.<br>\n\nIn 1969, Thiru V. Subbiah Pillai for Literature & Education Service was honoured by the Indian Government with Padma Shri. He was keen in translating in pure tamil, the same was named as Thamarai Chelvar and he was called as Thamarai Chelvar V. Subbiah Pillai.\nAfter the demise of Padma Shri V.Subbiah Pillai R.Muthukumaraswamy took charge as MD of Kazhagam. He was the conference secretary of the 5th International Tamil Conference which was held at Madurai Kamaraj University, Madurai under the able leadership of then Chief Minister Dr.MGR and he was the souvenir committee member of the 2nd International Tamil Conference which was held at Madras which was conducted by our then Chief Minister Thiru. C.N. Annadurai. Thiru R.Muthukumaraswamy was the President of BAPASI, The Booksellers' & Publishers' Association of South India Chennai Book Fair in the year 2004 \u2013 2005[1]<br>\n\nThe company has published books on Tamil Sangam Literature, Tirukkural Thelivurai by Mu.Va., Kazhaga Tamil Dictionary, Kazhaga Tamil English Dictionary, Kazhaga English Tamil Dictionary, Thirumanthiram with Ramanatha Pulavar Prose, Thiruvasagam with Ramanatha Pulavar Prose, etc. Works by Devaneya Pavanar and M. S. Purnalingam Pillai have also been published through this publishing house. The most famous title of this publishing house is Thirukkural Thelivurai written by a great Tamil Scholar Mu. Varadarajan.\nThe Kazhagam is now entering 100th year of celebration.\n\nRecognition\nIn 1969, Sri V. Subbiah Pillai for Literature & Education Service was honoured by the Indian Government with [[Padma Shri Awards (1960\u20131969)]].\n\n\n{{unreferenced|date=August 2017}}\n{{notability|date=August 2017}}\n'''The South India Saiva Siddhantha Works Publishing Society Tinnevely Ltd.''' (also known as '''Kazhagam''') is a Tamil book publishing company.\n\n== Books Published ==\n* Cattanar's [[Manimekalai]] - P. Pandian (Bacon), Manimekalai translated from the Tamil in English, Madras: South India Saiva Siddhanta Works Publishing Society Ltd., 1989\n* Thirukural Thelivurai Mu.Varadarajanar \n* Nalvar Varalaru\n* Kazhagam Tamil English Dictionary\n* Kazhagam Tamil Purananooru Tamil Ilakanam\n* Kazhagam Senthamil Selvi - Monthly Magazine\n* Kazhagam Tamil Agarathi\n* Kazhagam Tamil Ilakkanam\n* Kazhagam Tamil Vina Vidai\n* Thirumanthiram prose by Pulavar Ramanatha Pillai\n* Thiruvasagam prose by Pulavar Ramanatha Pillai\n* Thirukkovaiyar puthiya vilakkavuraiyudan\n* 63 Nayanmargal Varalaru\n* Sanga Ilakkiyam (Muzhimaiyuma Uraiyudan)\n* Ettu Thogai\n* Pathu Paattu\n* Pathinen Keezhkanakku\n* Sillapathikaram prose by Po. Ve Somasundaranar\n* Manimegalai with Prose\n* Tholkappiyam Ezhuthu Sol Porul\n* Thiruppugazh with Chengalvaraya Pillai Prose\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Book publishing companies of India]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "replaced: Books Published \u2192 Books published,typo(s) fixed: tamil \u2192 Tamil (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_India_Saiva_Siddhanta_Works_Publishing_Society_Ltd."}
